        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:13PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 313 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Malvern, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Benton...                         Malvern...
Haskell...                        Rockport...
Traskwood...                      Tull...
Poyen...                          Perla...
Lonsdale...                       Donaldson...
Magnet Cove...                    Fenter...
Nance...                          Social Hill...
Gifford...                        Shaw...
Glen Rose...                      Crows...
Midway in Hot Spring County...    Lake Catherine State Park...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
